    "text": "The WorldLines paper introduces memory-to-plan translation as a concrete algorithmic step to reconstruct world states from history, not as an abstract subproblem definition.",
    "topic": "definition in paper"
  },
  {
    "text": "The term 'subproblem' is not used in the WorldLines paper to characterize memory-to-plan translation; it is treated as a technical component within the system architecture.",
    "topic": "terminology used"
  },
  {
    "text": "The conditions of partial observability and overwritten world states are what necessitate memory-to-plan translation; the translation does not have a defined role or meaning in WorldLines outside those conditions.",
    "topic": "dependency on conditions"
  }
